# Domain Model Rules

## Pure Domain

- `packages/core/` has ZERO npm dependencies. Only TypeScript standard library.
- Domain models are interfaces, not classes. Use factory functions for creation.
- No framework imports (React, Zustand, Tauri, etc.) anywhere in this package.

## Ports Are Interfaces

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Port as interface in packages/core/src/ports/outbound/
export interface NoteRepository {
  findById(id: ULID): Promise<Note | null>
  save(note: Note): Promise<void>
}

// ❌ BAD: Concrete implementation in core
import Database from 'better-sqlite3'
export class SqliteNoteRepository { /* ... */ }
```

## Use Cases

- One file per use case (e.g., `create-note.ts`, `search-notes.ts`).
- Each use case is a function (or class) that accepts ports via constructor/parameter injection.
- Use cases return `Result<T, E>` for all operations.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Use case with injected ports
export function createNote(
  repo: NoteRepository,
  eventStore: EventStore,
) {
  return async (params: CreateNoteParams): Promise<Result<Note, ValidationError>> => {
    const validation = CreateNoteSchema.safeParse(params)
    if (!validation.success) return err(new ValidationError(validation.error))

    const note = buildNote(validation.data)
    await repo.save(note)
    await eventStore.append({ type: 'note.created', entityId: note.id, payload: note })
    return ok(note)
  }
}
```

## Validation

- All input validation uses Zod schemas defined in `packages/core/src/validation/`.
- Schemas are the single source of truth for both TypeScript types and runtime validation.
- Domain models may have invariants enforced in factory functions.

## Events

- All state changes emit domain events via `EventStore.append()`.
- Events are typed with the `EventType` union.
- Events are append-only — never modified or deleted.
